Colombian Stocks: Almacenes Exito Falls; Canacol Energy Rises

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-09-01T20:48:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/colombian-stocks-almacenes-exito-falls-canacol-energy-rises.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 0.4 percent to 13,470.37, while the
Colcap Index was little changed at 1,642.90.  Almacenes Exito SA (EXITO)  ,  Colombia ’s biggest retailer,
fell 1.8 percent to 23,040 pesos. The company said yesterday it
will offer shares in the local market at an 8.1 percent discount
from the Aug. 30 closing price.  The Medellin-based company will offer to sell 114.27
million shares at 21,900 pesos each, it said in a regulatory
filing yesterday.  Canacol Energy Ltd. (CNEC)  , the Toronto-based  oil
company  with fields in Colombia, rose 1.2 percent to 1,630
pesos. Canacol said it was awarded a contract from Ecopetrol SA,
Colombia’s biggest oil company, to buy gas and gas liquids from
the Rancho Hermoso field in the Llanos basin, according to a
regulatory filing today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
 bschmidt16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  